summary: The eighth and final season of Game of Thrones doesn’t have a release date yet, but it’s confirmed to be in the first half of...
caption:
The eighth and final season of Game of Thrones doesn’t have a release date yet, but it’s confirmed to be in the first half of 2019!❄️
HBO has also confirmed that they’re only developing 1 prequel series at the moment, which is going to focus on “The Long Night,” thousands of years before the events of GOT, when humans first fought the White Walkers.
Besides that, HBO doesn’t plan to develop any more Game of Thrones prequel/spin-off series right now (but that could change in the future).
Nothing’s official yet, but I’d say you can expect the new season either April/May/June 2019, and the spin-off series late 2020!
❄️
UPDATE: An actor from GOT who was at LFCC said that season 8 will be released in either April or May 2019! We already know that it’ll be released during the first half of 2019 as HBO confirmed, but now we actually have a timeframe!
